### Description

Angular v19 - using standalone

Currently to create a service, one approach is to use @Injectable({providedIn:'root'})

```
@Injectable({providedIn:'root'})
export class  MyService {
 }
```

### Proposed solution

 To align with Angular team's goal to reduce boilerplate code and code verbosity, can consider introducing a new annotation that is a concise version of @Injectable({providedIn:'root'})
FOr example



```
@RootInjectable()
export class  MyService {
 }
```




